-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Casino, Hays, Aviva 
-- 
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 01:51AM EST
-- None



Dec 8 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Casino and Hays Plc, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Casino <CASP.PA>: HSBC cuts to neutral from overweight; price target to 85 euros * Hays Plc <HAYS.L>: Barclays raises price target to 150p from 145p; rating overweight* Aviva Plc <AV.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 608p from 585p; rating buy  Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Aviva Plc <AV.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 608p from 585p; rating buy   * BAE Systems <BAES.L>: JP Morgan raises price target to 400p from 350p; rating underweight * Casino <CASP.PA>: HSBC cuts to neutral from overweight; price target to 85 euros  * Cobham <COB.L>: JP Morgan raises price target to 305p from 290p; rating neutral   * DS Smith Plc <SMDS.L>: Jefferies raises target price to 300p from 280p; rating hold   * Hays Plc <HAYS.L>: Barclays raises price target to 150p from 145p; rating overweight   * Qinetiq <QQ.L>: JP Morgan cuts price target to 210p from 225p; rating neutral  * Rallye <GENC.PA>: HSBC cuts price target to 37 euros from 50 euros; rating overweight   * Ultra Electronics <ULE.L>: JP Morgan cuts target to 1,890p from 1,970p; rating neutral